sec.p:
Diagnostic criteria for DPB proposed in 1998 10 by a working group of the Ministry of Health and Welfare of Japan are as follows:
persistent cough, sputum and exertional dyspnea;
history of or current chronic sinusitis;
bilateral diffuse small nodular shadows on a plain chest X-ray film or centrilobular micronodules on chest CT images;
coarse crackles;
FEV1/FVC less than 70% and PaO2 less than 80 mmHg;
titer of cold hemagglutinin equal to or higher than 64.
